Former acting Director General of the Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency (NIMASA), Calistus Obi admitted in court that he used part of the money he looted from NIMASA to build a hotel. Obi who is standing trails on a case of fraud said the hotel was constructed by Seastroke international and it is located somewhere in Asaba but he can’t remember the address. “I used part of the money to build my hotel constructed by Seastroke International. But the money has since been refunded to the EFCC. “The hotel is located somewhere in Asaba, Delta State. I can’t recollect the address now. The building is completed and is already functioning. The title documents of the hotel is being processed but I have the Certificate of Occupancy and I can produce it before the court.” Obi however revealed to the court that he had since refunded the money to the Economic and financial commission (EFCC). Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook